I'm not sure whether this feature should be in express or connect, as express has the ability to mount one application to another, like following: 

```
var app = express();
var submodule = express();
app.use('/subpath', submodule);
```

that's great, and can make file easily to managed. But unfortunately, this way is not work perfect in many situations. for example:

```
var app = express();
var submodule = express();
app.use('/submodule/:param', submodule);
```

Then this will only match exactly '/submodule/:param' but not '/submodule/xxx'. yes, I can do it like: 

```
app.use(''/submodule', function(..)  { 
      ... anything that handle the param by my self
});
```

the function is easy. but if express is targeting to make application modular and advise people to use mount, then that feature is one I prefer to be made inside express ranther than project code.

